  "response": "There are countless great English songs across various genres, but here are some timeless classics and popular favorites that many consider among the best:\n\n1. **\"Bohemian Rhapsody\"** by Queen\n2. **\"Imagine\"** by John Lennon\n3. **\"Stairway to Heaven\"** by Led Zeppelin\n4. **\"Hotel California\"** by Eagles\n5. **\"Hey Jude\"** by The Beatles\n6. **\"Billie Jean\"** by Michael Jackson\n7. **\"Like a Rolling Stone\"** by Bob Dylan\n8. **\"Smells Like Teen Spirit\"** by Nirvana\n9. **\"Shape of You\"** by Ed Sheeran\n10. **\"Rolling in the Deep\"** by Adele\n\nThese songs span various decades and styles, showcasing the diversity and talent found in English-language music. What's considered the \"best\" can be highly subjective, so preferences vary widely!",
